					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, I don't know much about $2003 and $2004, as those are definitely the most obscure registers on the NES hardware even today. I just know FCEUltra isn't that accurate, so very likely it's a bug in the source, and Nintendulator and Nestopia are the 2 most accurate emulators arround, so its more likely they are right.
<br />
<br />Also, Micro Machines relies on $2004 reads during rendering, that's really obscure, and so. I don't know but maybe FCEUltra did something hackish to get this (unlicenced) game to work even if it breaks the real logic.</div>

